I"ı<p>In macOS Sierra the setting for ‚Äú<em>Allow apps download from</em>‚Äù is missing the <em>Anywhere</em> option. To fix this, Gatekeeper needs to be disabled.</p>

<ol>
  <li>Close <em>System Preferences</em></li>
  <li>Run <code class="highlighter-rouge">sudo spctl --master-disable</code></li>
  <li>Now the <em>Anywhere</em> option shows up and is selected automatically in the <em>System Preference -&gt; Security &amp; Privacy</em>-panel</li>
</ol>

<blockquote>
  <p><em>Note</em>: To re-enable Gatekeeper, run <code class="highlighter-rouge">sudo spctl --master-enable</code>.</p>
</blockquote>

